title: Appointments to Research Council
content_text:
p>
	The Government today (September 14) announced the appointment of two new 
	members and re-appointment of 15 serving members to the Research Council for 
	a term of two years with effect from October 1, 2015. The two new members are the Director of the Jockey Club School of Public 
	Health and Primary Care of the Chinese University of Hong Kong, Professor 
	Yeoh Eng-kiong, and Consultant Physician of the Department of Medicine and 
	Geriatrics of Princess Margaret Hospital Dr Yu Wai-cho. They will succeed

Geriatrics of Princess Margaret Hospital Dr Yu Wai-cho. They will succeed 
	Professor Sian Griffiths and Dr Patrick Li Chung-ki, who have served on the 
	Council for six years. The Secretary for Food and Health (SFH), Dr Ko Wing-man, said he was 
	grateful to the two outgoing members for their dedication and invaluable 
	contribution to the work of the Research Council. He also thanked the two 
	new members for accepting the appointment. The Research Council, chaired by the SFH, is responsible for providing

strategic guidance for funding health and medical research, and overseeing the administration of the Health and Medical Research Fund including the allocation of funds for approved research projects.
